Cipla, Impala Platinum and Massmart May Move: South Africa Equity Preview

-- B y   R o b e r t   B r a n d
-- 
2011-08-24T22:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/cipla-impala-platinum-massmart-south-africa-equity-preview.html
The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index stock index rose
344.73, or 1.2 percent, to 29,604.59 in Johannesburg.  Cipla Medpro South Africa Ltd. (CMP)  : The maker of
prescription medicines reports earnings for the six months
through June. The company said on Aug. 11 earnings per share
rose from 68 percent to 75 percent compared with a year earlier.
The shares rose 2 cents, or 0.3 percent, to 6.27 rand.  Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP)  : The worldâ€™s second-
biggest platinum miner reports earnings for the year through
June. The company said on Aug. 12 earnings per share advanced as
much as 42 percent compared with 7.86 rand a year earlier. The
stock climbed 2.40 rand, or 1.4 percent, to 169.90 rand.  Massmart Holdings Ltd. (MSM)  : The South African retailer
controlled by Wal-Mart Stores Inc. reports earnings for the 52
weeks ended June 26. The company said on July 25 earnings per
share declined as much as 33 percent compared with a year
earlier. The shares rose 99 cents, or 0.7 percent, to 150.99
rand.  Woolworths Holdings Ltd. (WHL SJ): The clothing and food
retailer reports earnings for the year ended June 26, after
saying on July 19 earnings per share rose as much as 30 percent
from a year earlier. The stock gained 50 cents, or 1.6 percent,
to 32.10 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
